The following page by ChristianCoseru explains how to do Sanskrit
Unicode text processing:  It describes how to get your Emacs and LaTeX
configured for processing Sanskrit in Unicode. The assumption is that
you already have a more recent GNU/Linux distribution with Emacs, Mule and
LaTeX/teTeX installed.

* http://www.cofc.edu/~coseruc/unicode/
* http://www.anu.edu.au/asianstudies/ahcen/coseru/unicode/ - this link appears to be dead.


This page explains how to use emacs with the CSX encoding system for Sanskrit

* ftp://bombay.oriental.cam.ac.uk/pub/john/software/fonts/csx_unix/README

